Software Mastery:
       This is non-negotiable. You must be proficient in the Adobe Creative Suite (Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign) .
       For digital roles, tools like Figma and Sketch are essential . Knowledge of After Effects for motion graphics is a major plus .

Core Design Principles:
           Go beyond "making it look good." You need a deep understanding of typography, color theory, layout, hierarchy, and composition .

Print & Digital Expertise: Understand the differences. Print design requires knowledge of CMYK color modes, bleeds, and prepress processes.
          Digital design demands an understanding of UI/UX principles, accessibility (WCAG), and responsive design .

Branding: Learn how to build a cohesive visual identity system (logos, color palettes, typography) that communicates a brand's values 
         across all platforms .
